node.text:
I recently started following this bomb.com self help coach on my personal Instagram account. @therealjoirizarry 

Her daily convos/advice/ viewpoints are spot on in this stage of growth and healing. 

This particular post resonates with me as I started setting hella boundaries. Now I can identify that empty feeling, the loss that she speaks of. Maybe you can relate?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on September 09, 2021 tagging @jaronmyers, and @tanner_hamilton22. May be a Twitter screenshot of text that says 'Viral Tweets Jaron Myers @jaronmyers We're all so emotionally damaged from this last year and a half that Steve from Blue's Clues was like" have to address the nation" 11:47AM AM 9/8/21 Twitter for iPhone 25.2K Retweets 608 Quote Tweets 149K Likes'.

node.text:
This made me laugh so hard, I swear I needed that closure from Steve and I’m glad I got it. Maybe he can close the time rift if what’s been a crazy year….emotionally I’ve grown because I’ve had too. Navigating the waters of these last 2-3 years has been hard for everyone but I’m proud of you for continuing to keep going. Have a beautiful day. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
📸 = @jaronmyers
.
.
.

I needed this today, maybe someone you know needs it too. You are amazing, and whatever you do today I hope you do it the best you can. Even if you take a day off from society, it’s okay you can always start tomorrow. Grind culture can be toxic sometimes. Take care of yourself. - @tanner_hamilton22

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says 'hattie gladwell @hatttiegladwell Just because a person is okay today doesn't mean they'll be okay tomorrow. Mental illness can strike at any time. So please don't say 'well you were fine yesterday', because mental illness doesn't care about timing. And a person smiling doesn't mean they're suffering any less.'.

node.text:
We don’t pick the days we have to fight the battle. Like, “oh today’s Tuesday, I won’t be mentally unstable.”

We don’t pick that moment that the memory or trigger hits us and we unravel. 

Mental illness doesn’t follow a timeline and so many of us have learned to smile or act “normal” during an episode.  The roadmap for a mental health issue looks different for everyone. 

We need grace, and understanding, and sometimes just a little space. - @therealjoirizarry 

📸 @hattiegladwell on Twitter 
.
.
.
.
.

node.text:
I used to barely talk about how I’m feeling because I got left feeling like this so much. I’ve gotten better about opening up but only to the right people…if you are in my circle just know I appreciate you listening to me and I am sure you know I would do the same for you. I hope everyone has a beautiful Tuesday. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'My brain recording my good memories My brain recording my cringe memories'.

node.text:
Why is that we vividly remember every cringe worthy memory that we have made in our lifetime?

And why do we remember them every time we try to go to sleep at night? 

Why can I barely remember something good that happened just yesterday? 

Just, why? - @therealjoirizarry 
.
.
.
.
.
#somanyunansweredquestions #overthinking #iamanoverthinker #toomanyrandomthoughts #racingthoughts😣 #mentalhealthadvocate💚 #mentalhealthmemes🖤 #suicideawarenessmonth #safeplaceinsideyourhead

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says 'mom @thewildwatsons If a friend hasn't responded to my text but see them active on social media, it's probably because they are overtired overworked and taking a well-deserved break to scroll. You're not entitled to someone's down time. True friends understand that you can't pour from an empty cup'.

node.text:
That’s me, I’m the friend. 

I’m not gonna lie. When I need a break from reality, I turn to media and leave out the social part. Sometimes I wanna be alone and just meme hunt and laugh or find content that helps me get my head back on straight. It doesn’t mean I want to comment or engage, i just wanna be somewhere in the background. 

So give your friends like me one small break. Give them time and space to unwind. 

Now back to meme hunting …… 😆 @therealjoirizarry 

📸 @thewildwatsons on Twitter 
.
.
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on September 05, 2021 tagging @tanner_hamilton22. May be an image of text that says '"can u multitask" yes actually i am losing my mind and chilling at the same time'.

node.text:
Today I am trying to relax, I feel like I’ve been working for a few months in a row. Even on my days off it feels like I’ve got a million things to do. Some days I really do feel like losing my mind but…today is not that day. I’ve closed my work computer, turned on some video games, got some junk food and now I’m just gaming till the end of the day. I will not be multitasking today, and I’m not even going to apologize for that. - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#takeabreak #everyonedeservesabreak #asafeplaceinsideyourhead #keepgoing #mentalhealth #sundayvibes #sundayfunday #youareloved #timetoturnoffthebrain #itsalot #keepgoing #iwillnotapologize

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by A Safe Place Inside Your Head on September 05, 2021 tagging @tanner_hamilton22. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'When you try to explain your anxiety to someone and they reply with "don't worry, you'll be fine"'.

node.text:
I tell people I have social anxiety…some people tell me I need to be more social and it will go away. I’m not sure that’s how that works 🤔. It’s getting better though, but I’ll move at my own speed. Just a heads up though if someone talks to you about their anxiety, just listen and meet them where they are at. Advice like the one in the meme isn’t optimal and can cause feelings of invalidation. I personally prefer “I’m here for you, I understand and see why you feel that way” better. Anyone else feel this way? - @tanner_hamilton22 
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by A Safe Place Inside Your Head in Austin, Texas with @this.is.chronic.pain. May be an image of text that says 'ines @btsklein "social anxiety is an excuse" would you enjoy being scared of ordering a damn menu? hearing people laughing and instantly thinking they're laughing at you? counting your money a hundred times to make sure you don't make a fool out of yourself? this. is. not. a. fcking ok'.

node.text:
It’s not a fuckin joke to be mentally ill. Social anxiety is crippling. 

It’s surprising how many people just don’t understand mental illness 🤦🏼‍♀️ 

I’m sorry if this is you. It’s me too, and so many of my friends. Please know you are not alone. You are seen and heard.  And we’re standing right beside you, holding you up. - @therealjoirizarry 

@this.is.chronic.pain 

📸 @btsklein on Twitter
